Two vulnerabilities were reported in Oracle Database. A local user can access data on the target system. A remote authenticated user can gain elevated privileges.
A remote authenticated user can exploit a flaw in the OJVM component to gain elevated privileges [CVE-2017-3310].

A local user can exploit a flaw in the RDBMS Security component to partially access data [CVE-2017-3240].

